    {
      "id": "welcome-hero",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Welcome to Twilite",
      "position": {
        "x": 100,
        "y": -300
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "#1976d2",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "bottom",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        {
          "key": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "type": "any"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "key": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "type": "content"
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Welcome to Twilite \u2728\n\n**A persistent graph workspace where ideas connect and evolve.**\n\nTwilight is a visual thinking environment built on graphs. Every node is a thought, every edge is a relationship, and the whole canvas is your workspace.\n\n## What makes Twilite different?\n\n- **Persistent state** - Your graph is the source of truth\n- **Semantic connections** - Edges carry meaning and type\n- **Contract-driven** - Manifests define intent and authority\n- **Incremental updates** - Small, targeted changes preserve history\n\nExplore the nodes below to get started! \ud83d\udc47",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "core-concepts",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Core Concepts",
      "position": {
        "x": -200,
        "y": 100
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 420,
      "color": "#1976d2",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "flow",
          "position": {
            "side": "top",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        {
          "key": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "type": "flow"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "key": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "type": "content"
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Core Concepts\n\n### Nodes\nThe atoms of your workspace. Each node has:\n- **Type** - What kind of thing it is\n- **Data** - Its actual content\n- **Ports** - Connection points\n- **ID** - Permanent identity\n\n### Edges\nTyped relationships between nodes:\n- `sequence` - Ordering/flow\n- `reference` - Citations/links\n- `dependency` - Requirements\n- `hierarchy` - Parent/child\n\n### Manifest\nThe contract that defines:\n- **Intent** - What this graph is for\n- **Authority** - Who can modify it\n- **Constraints** - What rules apply\n\n### State Deltas\nChanges happen through commands:\n- `createNodes` / `createEdges`\n- `update` / `delete`\n- `transaction` for atomic updates",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "quick-start",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Quick Start Guide",
      "position": {
        "x": 250,
        "y": 100
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 380,
      "color": "#1976d2",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "flow",
          "position": {
            "side": "top",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        {
          "key": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "type": "flow"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "key": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "type": "content"
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Quick Start\n\n### 1. Inspect Before Acting\nAlways look at existing nodes and the Manifest before making changes.\n\n### 2. Use State Deltas\nNever emit a full graph. Use targeted commands:\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"createNodes\",\n  \"nodes\": [/* ... */]\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Preserve Identity\nKeep existing IDs. Never delete+recreate.\n\n### 4. Create in Order\n1. Nodes first\n2. Then edges\n3. Finally clusters\n\n### 5. Validate Semantics\nAsk: \"Does this graph make sense for its declared purpose?\"\n\n### 6. When Uncertain, Ask\nClarity beats speed. Append a note if you're unsure.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": ""
      }
    },
